originalText.text: The teachers are actually decent, people really just need to give the same respect back to the teachers. Some students here are annoying and narcissistic, they act like the boss and they’re basically obnoxious tiktok kids. Ms. Colleen (the principal) on the other hand isn’t good, if someone got in trouble for throwing stuff out the window from the 9th floor, she would give them  after school detention for 15-30 minutes (this actually happened). Honestly it would be way worse if there weren’t those yondr poaches or whatever it’s called.

originalText.text: My daughter is blossoming at this school. The work is challenging and it allows her to think critically. originalText.text: My daughter loves this school. It is amazing and the staff members are really kind. She already loves it and she is only in 6th grade. Every girl would surely enjoy this school. I can also relax knowing that my daughter is in a safe environment. They also have big sisters who are 9th graders. They are really supportive of each other. This school is also encouraging and has a lot of trust in the girls.

originalText.text: Academic wise this school is known for producing scholars! They have a high college acceptance rate & the work prepares you for college. As far as Administration, they're terrible! My daughter has been getting bullied in and outside the school and the Principal and staff have done a terrible job at helping with this situation. First off their school phones have not "worked" for a yr already so you can never get through to anyone. No one responds to emails, they do not inform you when your child is pulled out of class. When meeting with the parents and staff the principal was completely unprofessional, yelling at us and even got in our faces!! My daughter is still dealing dealing with this issue and we have even brought it to the attention of the police. I am now filing a report with the DOE as well. I now feel like I have no choice but to remove her from this school and let these cowards rob her of a wonderful opportunity all because of a terrible principal and vice principal.
